title: Tyson Fresh Meats Recalls Beef Products Due To Possible E. Coli O157:H7 Contamination
summary: WASHINGTON, June 3, 2015 Tyson Fresh Meats, a Dakota City, Neb., establishment, is recalling approximately 16,000 pounds of ground beef products that may be contaminated with E. coli O157:H7, the U.S. Department of Agricultures Food Safety and Inspection Service (FSIS) announced today.The ground beef items...
